1481","1480":"1480","Brislington, , Somerset, England":"Brislington, Bristol, England, United Kingdom","Maidenhead, Windsor and Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Margaret","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Margaret</i>, which is derived via French from Greek <i>margaritēs</i> ‘pearl’."],"variants":[{"name":"Morgret","meanings":["German (Lower Saxony): variant of <b>Margret</b>, a habitational name from any of the places called Margareth(en), which in turn are named with the female saint's name <i>Margaretha</i>, see   Margaret  .","Americanized form of German   Marquardt  . Compare   Morgart  ."]},{"name":"Pogson","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): metronymic from the Middle English female personal name <i>Pog</i>, a variant of <i>Mog</i>, a pet form of   Margaret  ."]},{"name":"Metten","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German August, Hans.","German: habitational name from a place called Metten in Westphalia.","Flemish (Belgian Limburg) and Dutch: metronymic from the female personal name <i>Mette</i>, a pet form of Margaretha (see   Margaret  )."]},{"name":"Margot","meanings":["French and English: from the French and Middle English female personal name <i>Margot</i>, a pet form of French <i>Marguerite</i>, English   Margaret  . In England it is in part of Huguenot origin.","English: occasionally perhaps from the Old French male personal name <i>Margot</i> (ancient Germanic <i>Margot</i>, composed of the elements <i>marh-</i> ‘war horse’ or <i>mar-</i> ‘famous’ + <i>got-</i>, the base of the ethnic name ‘Goth’)."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: Bitter; Marion is the French form."],"variants":[{"name":"Marion","meanings":["Originally a medieval French diminutive form of   Marie  , introduced to Britain in the Middle Ages. In some places it was taken as a pet form of   Margaret   or   Margery .  As a male name, it is an altered form of the Continental male name <i>Marian</i>, a derivative of Latin <i>Marianus</i> (from   Marius  ), but is now rarely, if ever, used. It was the birth name of the American film star  John Wayne  (  1907–79 )."]},{"name":"Marcia","meanings":["Often used as a feminine equivalent of   Mark  , but in fact a feminine form of <i>Marcius</i>, itself a derivative of   Marcus .  One  St Marcia  is commemorated in a group with Felix, Luciolus, Fortunatus, and others; another with Zenais, Cyria, and Valeria; and a third with Ariston, Crescentian, Eutychian, Urban, Vitalis, Justus, Felicissimus, Felix, and Symphorosa. None is individually very famous."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Margaret was born in 1481, in Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Richard Appleforde. She died in 1579, in her hometown, at the age of 98."},"et":{"1481–1579":"1481–1579","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1499–1579":"1499–1579","1579":"1579","1523":"1523","1499":"1499","about 1523":"umbes 1523","1481":"1481","1480":"1480","Brislington, , Somerset, England":"Brislington, Bristol, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Maidenhead, Windsor and Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Maidenhead, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bradford-on-Avon, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1481–1579":"1481–1579","1480–1523":"1480–1523","1499–1579":"1499–1579","1579":"1579","1523":"1523","1499":"1499","about 1523":"noin 1523","1481":"1481","1480":"1480","Brislington, , Somerset, England":"Brislington, Bristol, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Maidenhead, Windsor and Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Maidenhead, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bradford-on-Avon, W